ROOT CAUSE: The bug occurs because `PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON` is set inside an active database transaction (the one created by Drizzle's migrator). In SQLite, pragmas are ignored when the database is in a transaction; they only take effect outside of transactions. Therefore, when the migration runs `PRAGMA foreign_keys = OFF`, it has no effect since a transaction is already open. The subsequent `DROP TABLE` then cascades and deletes all related data in `task_events`.

FIX:
```ts
import { migrate } from "drizzle-orm/better-sqlite3/migrator";
import { db, sqlite } from "./client.js";

export function runMigrations(): void {
    // Disable FK enforcement at connection level (outside any transaction)
    sqlite.pragma("foreign_keys = OFF");

    try {
        migrate(db, { migrationsFolder: "...drizzle" });
    } finally {
        // Restore FK enforcement after migrations complete
        sqlite.pragma("foreign_keys = ON");
    }
}
```

CAVEAT: None

